doc.previous: Services, including those related to commerce, transportation, and banking, have become increasingly important. Tourism is a small but significant component of the local economy[36][37] with international visitors totaling almost 3 million in 2008.[38] Taipei has many top tourist attractions and contributes a significant amount to the US$6.8 billion tourism industry in Taiwan.[39] National brands such as ASUS,[40] Chunghwa Telecom,[41] Mandarin Airlines,[42] Tatung,[43] and Uni Air,[44][45] D-Link [46] are headquartered in Taipei City.
